Lime Pound Cake
  --Laura, Little House, Big Alaska

1 c unsalted butter
2 c sugar
3 limes
4 eggs
3 c flour
1/2 tsp baking soda
1/2 tsp baking powder
3/4 c buttermilk or 1 tbsp vinegar + enough milk to equal 3/4 c
2 c powdered sugar

Preheat oven to 350F. generously grease two 9×5" loaf pans. In the bowl of a stand mixer beat butter and sugar for 5 min or until it's light and fluffy. While it's beating zest the limes and then juice them. Add the lime zest to the sugar mixture. Add eggs mixing well after each addition. Stop the mixer and scrape down the sides of the bowl, make sure to scraped off the beater as well, the lime zest has a tendency to get hung up on it. Mix the flour with the baking soda and baking powder. Mix the milk with a 1/4 c of the lime juice, reserve the rest of the lime juice for the icing. Add 1/4 of the flour mix to the mixing bowl, follow it with 1/3 of the liquid, repeat beginning and ending with the flour, pulse between addition. Scraped down the bowl and mix by hand a few times to make sure everything is well combined. Divide the batter between the greased loaf pans. Bake for 45 min or until a toothpick comes out clean. Cool for 15 min, then remove from the pans and cool completely. Once cooled mix the two cups of powdered sugar with 2-3 tbsp of the leftover lime juice for a glaze, start with the smallest amount adding small amounts until the glaze is thin enough to drizzle and thick enough to cling.

